762
00:48:26.343 --> 00:48:28.596
Correct...
73-K Orlando. Out.

763
00:48:44.486 --> 00:48:47.323
(inhales. exhales)

764
00:48:47.406 --> 00:48:48.532
Nothin'?

765
00:48:49.783 --> 00:48:52.369
Is there any chance
it's comin' in at night?

766
00:48:52.453 --> 00:48:53.912
You're sleepin'. you miss it?

767
00:48:54.246 --> 00:48:55.831
Hm.

768
00:48:58.208 --> 00:49:01.003
When I'm sleeping.
Gabriela listens. or my son.

769
00:49:01.086 --> 00:49:04.048
The smart one. not the
other one. God bless him.

770
00:49:05.758 --> 00:49:08.010
If Tommy responded. we'd know.

771
00:49:08.093 --> 00:49:10.012
- And you're talkin' to the tower?
- Every day.

772
00:49:10.095 --> 00:49:11.906
They gave him your message.
they haven't seen or heard

773
00:49:11.930 --> 00:49:14.683
from him since. and that's it.

774
00:49:14.767 --> 00:49:17.311
- It hasn't been that long.
- It's been three weeks.

775
00:49:17.394 --> 00:49:19.274
It's never taken him
more than a day to respond.

776
00:49:21.231 --> 00:49:22.274
I'm sure he's okay.

777
00:49:28.447 --> 00:49:29.527
Show me where the tower is.

778
00:49:31.033 --> 00:49:32.159
Oh. you can't be serious.

779
00:49:34.078 --> 00:49:35.704
J-Joel. it's in Wyoming.

780
00:49:35.788 --> 00:49:38.874
Uh. all-all this open country?

781
00:49:38.958 --> 00:49:40.060
I mean. you're a capable guy.

782
00:49:40.084 --> 00:49:43.379
but there are worse things
than Infected out there.

783
00:49:43.462 --> 00:49:45.130
I hear everything on this.

784
00:49:45.214 --> 00:49:47.091
There are raiders.
there are slavers...

785
00:49:47.174 --> 00:49:48.414
But you're "sure" Tommy's okay?

786
00:49:48.467 --> 00:49:51.387
♪ ♪

787
00:49:53.138 --> 00:49:54.473
(sighs)

788
00:49:56.475 --> 00:49:57.893
It's. uh. it's the Cody tower...

789
00:50:00.187 --> 00:50:02.773
Q-Bar 4. but I don't
know exactly wh...

790
00:50:04.358 --> 00:50:06.110
(sighs)

791
00:50:09.154 --> 00:50:12.199
Next!

792
00:50:12.866 --> 00:50:13.909
♪ ♪

793
00:50:25.170 --> 00:50:27.172
(distant chatter)

794
00:50:39.893 --> 00:50:42.104
(light music plays)

795
00:50:51.196 --> 00:50:53.240
(unloading items)

796
00:51:05.711 --> 00:51:09.131
(uneasy music plays)

797
00:51:23.228 --> 00:51:26.273
(slams glass)

798
00:51:34.031 --> 00:51:37.075
(slams glass)

799
00:51:40.496 --> 00:51:44.291
♪ ♪

800
00:51:52.674 --> 00:51:53.735
(Tommy's voice echoes):
<i>You know what. Joel...</i>

801
00:51:53.759 --> 00:51:56.678
- (Sarah panting)
- Tommy:<i> Joel!</i>

802
00:51:59.681 --> 00:52:01.308
(door closes)

803
00:52:13.779 --> 00:52:16.448
(ambient street noise)

804
00:52:21.161 --> 00:52:23.121
(cookware clanking)

805
00:52:23.205 --> 00:52:25.833
(distant baby crying)

806
00:52:26.750 --> 00:52:29.336
(distant siren buzzing)

807
00:52:53.819 --> 00:52:57.281
I got jumped by a couple guys.

808
00:52:57.364 --> 00:52:59.533
- What guys?
- Just a couple teenagers.

809
00:52:59.616 --> 00:53:01.368
Said some shit.
probably shouldn't've.

810
00:53:03.495 --> 00:53:05.998
Come on. You know these
guys were born after the outbreak.

811
00:53:06.081 --> 00:53:08.333
Never learned how to argue.
They just start swingin'.

812
00:53:08.417 --> 00:53:10.252
Fuckin' 19-year-old
pieces of shit.

813
00:53:11.003 --> 00:53:13.005
It's a miracle you're alive.

814
00:53:14.006 --> 00:53:16.008
It's a miracle
any of us are alive.

815
00:53:18.468 --> 00:53:19.761
These aren't new.

816
00:53:20.095 --> 00:53:22.097
No.

817
00:53:22.180 --> 00:53:24.933
I was in FEDRA lockup all day.

818
00:53:26.226 --> 00:53:28.896
Anyway. it doesn't matter.

819
00:53:28.979 --> 00:53:30.459
- I need you to take a breath.
- What?

820
00:53:32.816 --> 00:53:34.818
- Joel...
- What?

821
00:53:36.987 --> 00:53:39.323
The guys who jumped me
were with Robert.

822
00:53:39.406 --> 00:53:41.283
He sold our battery
to someone else.

823
00:53:42.784 --> 00:53:46.121
Nothing's lost. Shit like
this is gonna happen.

824
00:53:46.204 --> 00:53:47.789
Now we just shake it off.

825
00:53:47.873 --> 00:53:50.250
and we go get our
cards back. or the battery.

826
00:53:50.334 --> 00:53:52.544
I need the battery. Tess.

827
00:53:52.628 --> 00:53:54.004
Truck's no good without one.

828
00:53:54.087 --> 00:53:55.189
and if I don't
get to Tommy soon.

829
00:53:55.213 --> 00:53:56.298
he's gonna die out there.

830
00:53:56.381 --> 00:53:57.215
Okay. fuck it.

831
00:53:57.299 --> 00:53:58.299
We get our money back

832
00:53:58.342 --> 00:53:59.051
and the battery.

833
00:53:59.134 --> 00:54:00.218
But. Joel. listen.

834
00:54:00.302 --> 00:54:02.304
Robert is terrified of you.

835
00:54:02.387 --> 00:54:04.139
So you march outta here
all Clint Eastwood.

836
00:54:04.222 --> 00:54:05.974
he's gonna get
wind of it and skip.

837
00:54:06.058 --> 00:54:08.310
I need you to take a breath.

838
00:54:14.024 --> 00:54:15.043
- Who'd he sell it to?
- Don't know.

839
00:54:15.067 --> 00:54:17.235
- Well. where is he?
- Don't know.

840
00:54:18.779 --> 00:54:20.614
Yet.

841
00:54:20.697 --> 00:54:23.742
But we're gonna
find out... quietly.

842
00:54:23.825 --> 00:54:26.495
Understand?

843
00:54:26.578 --> 00:54:28.789
Now I promised Robert
that you wouldn't hurt him.

844
00:54:30.082 --> 00:54:33.126
But I would very much
like for you to hurt him.

845
00:54:33.210 --> 00:54:36.171
So let's go hunt
that motherfucker down.

846
00:54:36.254 --> 00:54:38.090
and get our battery
and our truck.

847
00:54:38.173 --> 00:54:41.385
and then we'll go find Tommy.

848
00:54:41.468 --> 00:54:44.513
All right?

849
00:54:45.430 --> 00:54:48.475
All right.

850
00:54:52.980 --> 00:54:55.816
(indistinct chatter)

851
00:55:09.162 --> 00:55:11.581
The team in place
at Southeast 3?

852
00:55:13.166 --> 00:55:14.251
Kim: I held them back.

853
00:55:15.585 --> 00:55:17.379
I have some questions.

854
00:55:17.462 --> 00:55:18.672
Hm... Okay.

855
00:55:19.798 --> 00:55:22.259
We've been blowing up
meaningless FEDRA targets

856
00:55:22.342 --> 00:55:24.720
spread out all over
the QZ. for two weeks.

857
00:55:24.803 --> 00:55:26.847
We've already lost
four people. and we're...

858
00:55:27.973 --> 00:55:29.141
What's the point of this?

859
00:55:30.809 --> 00:55:32.394
Is that your question?

860
00:55:32.477 --> 00:55:33.311
That's one of them.

861
00:55:33.395 --> 00:55:35.564
My answer is to follow
fuckin' orders.

862
00:55:35.647 --> 00:55:37.542
And why do you have some
random girl locked in a room?

863
00:55:37.566 --> 00:55:40.318
And the guys you have
guarding her won't tell me shit?

864
00:55:40.402 --> 00:55:43.321
Our people are asking
what's going on.

865
00:55:43.405 --> 00:55:44.865
and I don't know
what to tell them.

866
00:55:44.948 --> 00:55:47.075
Tell them to follow
fuckin' orders.

867
00:55:47.159 --> 00:55:49.327
You two. go to Southeast 3. Now.

868
00:55:52.372 --> 00:55:54.708
(door opens. closes)

869
00:55:55.709 --> 00:55:57.419
- Kim.
- Marlene.

870
00:55:57.502 --> 00:56:00.088
We are in a war against
a military dictatorship

871
00:56:00.172 --> 00:56:01.923
to restore democracy
and freedom.

872
00:56:02.007 --> 00:56:02.924
Does that sound about right?

873
00:56:03.008 --> 00:56:04.051
- Yes?
- Are we winning?

874
00:56:04.134 --> 00:56:05.260
Are we beating FEDRA here?

875
00:56:05.343 --> 00:56:06.943
Are the Fireflies
beating FEDRA anywhere?

876
00:56:07.012 --> 00:56:08.197
- Rebellion takes time.
- You fight for 20 years

877
00:56:08.221 --> 00:56:10.932
and you get nowhere.
you're not a rebellion.

878
00:56:11.016 --> 00:56:13.810
Just spray paint.

879
00:56:13.894 --> 00:56:16.271
We're not hitting FEDRA
"all over" the QZ.

880
00:56:16.354 --> 00:56:19.983
We hit 'em here.
here. here. here. here.

881
00:56:20.650 --> 00:56:21.902
Where are we right now?

882
00:56:24.029 --> 00:56:26.239
I want FEDRA
everywhere but here.

883
00:56:26.323 --> 00:56:28.075
I want them as
distracted as possible

884
00:56:28.158 --> 00:56:29.951
because tonight.
every Firefly in Boston

885
00:56:30.035 --> 00:56:31.495
is gonna gather
in this building.

886
00:56:31.578 --> 00:56:33.872
and we are gonna leave
the QZ. Permanently.

887
00:56:35.082 --> 00:56:36.792
- We're quitting?
- No.

888
00:56:36.875 --> 00:56:39.961
We're taking that random
girl locked in that room west.

889
00:56:41.922 --> 00:56:44.091
From our guy in the
radio tower in Salem.

890
00:56:51.890 --> 00:56:54.184
Is this real?

891
00:56:54.893 --> 00:56:56.478
I believe it is.

892
00:56:59.898 --> 00:57:02.943
Keep it quiet.

893
00:57:04.528 --> 00:57:06.238
Whatever you need.

894
00:57:06.321 --> 00:57:07.739
Whatever it takes.

895
00:57:07.823 --> 00:57:09.741
We'll get her
where she needs to go.

896
00:57:19.793 --> 00:57:21.628
(indistinct chatter)

897
00:57:39.104 --> 00:57:41.982
Hey. friend.

898
00:57:42.065 --> 00:57:43.984
Don't worry.
I don't want anything.

899
00:57:44.067 --> 00:57:45.694
But if you're feelin' lost...

900
00:57:45.777 --> 00:57:48.137
You tell me to "look for the
light" and I'll break your jaw.

901
00:57:54.953 --> 00:57:56.997
(siren buzzes)

902
00:57:58.999 --> 00:58:03.044
Well. I mean. it cost us a couple
of cards. but. uh. we got him.

903
00:58:03.128 --> 00:58:05.481
He's supposedly takin' the
battery to a red-tagged building.

904
00:58:05.505 --> 00:58:09.551
But get this... corner
of Stillman and Cross.

905
00:58:09.634 --> 00:58:11.261
The one Miguel used to use.

906
00:58:11.344 --> 00:58:13.013
Yeah. I'm thinkin' so.

907
00:58:13.096 --> 00:58:14.282
I mean. we can take the
subway tunnel under Haymarket.

908
00:58:14.306 --> 00:58:16.683
get into the building
from below.

909
00:58:16.766 --> 00:58:18.894
and take Robert by surprise.

910
00:58:18.977 --> 00:58:20.270
Pay this fucker back.

911
00:58:21.146 --> 00:58:23.565
(manacle clanking)

912
00:58:25.233 --> 00:58:26.818
(grunting)

913
00:58:28.653 --> 00:58:31.698
Oh. my God.

914
00:58:32.824 --> 00:58:34.910
(spits)

915
00:58:34.993 --> 00:58:36.912
Agh! You fucker!

916
00:58:38.830 --> 00:58:40.707
(sighs)

917
00:58:40.790 --> 00:58:42.250
(door squeaks)

918
00:58:42.334 --> 00:58:45.795
- (door closes)
- One. two. three. four...

919
00:58:47.547 --> 00:58:49.132
(rain pattering)

920
00:59:13.031 --> 00:59:15.033
You're not scared.

921
00:59:18.078 --> 00:59:19.913
Then unlock me.

922
00:59:19.996 --> 00:59:21.581
How about we start
with "thank you"?

923
00:59:21.665 --> 00:59:22.958
For what?

924
00:59:23.041 --> 00:59:24.501
For saving your life?

925
00:59:24.584 --> 00:59:25.252
I am the one who told 'em
not to shoot you.

926
00:59:25.335 --> 00:59:28.171
- if you recall.
- (mutters) Yeah.

927
00:59:35.470 --> 00:59:37.806
Why did you stop them?

928
00:59:37.889 --> 00:59:38.974
We'll get to that.

929
00:59:53.071 --> 00:59:54.489
So... Veronica...

930
00:59:57.867 --> 00:59:59.160
how ya feelin'?

931
00:59:59.953 --> 01:00:01.997
The same.

932
01:00:03.164 --> 01:00:05.542
Is it gonna happen?

933
01:00:06.960 --> 01:00:08.753
No.

934
01:00:12.090 --> 01:00:13.216
So. can I go?

935
01:00:14.259 --> 01:00:15.010
No.

936
01:00:15.093 --> 01:00:17.095
I won't tell anyone
about any of this.

937
01:00:17.178 --> 01:00:18.346
I swear.

938
01:00:18.430 --> 01:00:19.514
Where you gonna go?

939
01:00:19.597 --> 01:00:21.266
Back to FEDRA military school?

940
01:00:21.349 --> 01:00:24.394
- You that anxious to be a soldier?
- You think I chose that place?

941
01:00:24.477 --> 01:00:26.271
They put me there
when I was a baby.

942
01:00:26.354 --> 01:00:27.605
It's for orphans.

943
01:00:27.689 --> 01:00:30.734
"They" didn't put you there.

944
01:00:31.484 --> 01:00:32.527
I did.

945
01:00:33.445 --> 01:00:36.489
Ellie.

946
01:00:37.490 --> 01:00:40.493
You my fucking mom or something?

947
01:00:40.577 --> 01:00:42.120
Do I look like your mom?

948
01:00:42.203 --> 01:00:45.332
Nooo. you do not.

949
01:00:46.166 --> 01:00:47.876
My name is Marlene.

950
01:00:47.959 --> 01:00:49.879
I'm the leader of the
Fireflies in the Boston QZ.

951
01:00:51.629 --> 01:00:53.590
Why would a terrorist
dump me with FEDRA?

952
01:00:53.673 --> 01:00:55.693
Because it's where you'd be
safest. and you were safe there

953
01:00:55.717 --> 01:00:56.051
until you decided to sneak out.

954
01:00:56.134 --> 01:00:57.761
And "terrorist"?

955
01:00:59.304 --> 01:01:00.722
Was Riley a terrorist?

956
01:01:03.558 --> 01:01:05.643
(solemn music plays)

957
01:01:17.614 --> 01:01:20.075
(voice breaking):
Why won't you let me go home?

958
01:01:23.328 --> 01:01:24.079
Because you have
a greater purpose

959
01:01:24.162 --> 01:01:25.642
than any of us
could've ever imagined.

960
01:01:27.665 --> 01:01:29.292
So we're leaving tonight.

961
01:01:29.376 --> 01:01:31.086
and we're taking you with us.

962
01:01:31.169 --> 01:01:32.504
(knocks on door)

963
01:01:33.755 --> 01:01:35.965
- Medic: He's here.
- Five minutes.

964
01:01:37.550 --> 01:01:40.345
(door closes)

965
01:01:40.428 --> 01:01:42.806
What I'm about to tell you
cannot be repeated to anyone.

966
01:01:43.598 --> 01:01:45.433
Because if you do...

967
01:01:45.517 --> 01:01:46.768
I assure you...

968
01:01:48.436 --> 01:01:50.021
you will die.

969
01:01:52.816 --> 01:01:53.983
(thundering)

970
01:02:01.074 --> 01:02:04.327
(tense music plays)

971
01:02:12.377 --> 01:02:13.503
Tess: Okay.

972
01:02:14.462 --> 01:02:15.922
Ready?

973
01:02:16.005 --> 01:02:19.050
Joel: Yeah.

974
01:02:21.886 --> 01:02:23.930
(water dripping)

975
01:02:24.013 --> 01:02:25.807
♪ ♪

976
01:02:34.274 --> 01:02:37.318
Oh. that's the one.

977
01:02:46.911 --> 01:02:48.746
(water dripping)

978
01:02:59.716 --> 01:03:01.676
Oh! Oh fuck.

979
01:03:01.759 --> 01:03:02.927
Oh shit.

980
01:03:05.054 --> 01:03:06.139
Joel: This one's done.

981
01:03:06.764 --> 01:03:07.849
(exhales)

982
01:03:08.641 --> 01:03:10.185
Yeah...

983
01:03:10.268 --> 01:03:11.519
I know. I just...

984
01:03:11.603 --> 01:03:13.146
I wasn't expecting it.

985
01:03:13.229 --> 01:03:14.772
Take it he wasn't
down here last time?

986
01:03:15.148 --> 01:03:16.941
No.

987
01:03:18.776 --> 01:03:22.864
You think he came down
after he was infected?

988
01:03:22.947 --> 01:03:26.326
(sighs) Well. maybe down
here is where he was infected.

989
01:03:30.914 --> 01:03:32.540
Let's keep movin'.

990
01:03:36.085 --> 01:03:38.171
♪ ♪

991
01:03:46.638 --> 01:03:49.057
Joel: It's like they reframed
the whole structure.

992
01:03:49.140 --> 01:03:50.558
Probably in the '80s.

993
01:03:50.642 --> 01:03:51.476
Everyone was cutting
down on apartment sizes

994
01:03:51.559 --> 01:03:54.229
- to sell more condos.
- Oh.

995
01:03:54.312 --> 01:03:58.942
"This has been 'Construction
Corner' with Joel Miller."

996
01:03:59.025 --> 01:04:00.944
- How far up we goin'?
- Uh...

997
01:04:02.946 --> 01:04:04.030
this far.

998
01:04:05.490 --> 01:04:06.741
(Tess grunts)

999
01:04:06.824 --> 01:04:11.704
So. this... this opens
into the ha-hallway.

1000
01:04:11.788 --> 01:04:13.828
What the fuck? Someone
put a piano in front of this?

1001
01:04:15.333 --> 01:04:17.585
(Joel sniffs)

1002
01:04:17.669 --> 01:04:19.003
You smell that?

1003
01:04:20.922 --> 01:04:23.007
Yeah... gunpowder.

1004
01:04:26.386 --> 01:04:28.012
♪ ♪

1005
01:04:29.514 --> 01:04:30.807
- Tess.
- (Tess grunts)

1006
01:04:51.703 --> 01:04:53.997
Tess:
Well. the battery's no good.

1007
01:04:54.080 --> 01:04:55.999
And he still tried to sell it.

1008
01:04:56.874 --> 01:04:57.959
Twice.

1009
01:04:59.043 --> 01:05:00.753
You greedy fuck.

1010
01:05:00.837 --> 01:05:02.297
(person winces)

1011
01:05:06.467 --> 01:05:08.886
(person grunts)

1012
01:05:09.554 --> 01:05:12.390
(indistinct chatter)

1013
01:05:13.891 --> 01:05:15.977
- (groaning)
- Marlene: Shit.

1014
01:05:16.060 --> 01:05:17.604
Oh God. Just...

1015
01:05:19.897 --> 01:05:22.483
- (groaning)
- Marlene: Oh shit. come on.

1016
01:05:22.567 --> 01:05:24.444
(heavy breathing)

1017
01:05:26.738 --> 01:05:28.323
(Ellie yells)

1018
01:05:28.823 --> 01:05:30.950
Fuck.
(panting)

1019
01:05:32.952 --> 01:05:33.995
Marlene: Joel?

1020
01:05:34.370 --> 01:05:36.205
Marlene?

1021
01:05:37.498 --> 01:05:40.335
- You okay?
- Yeah.

1022
01:05:42.837 --> 01:05:44.172
Marlene: Ellie...

1023
01:05:44.255 --> 01:05:45.548
Ellie!

1024
01:05:47.925 --> 01:05:49.862
- Oh shit!
- Marlene: No. it's okay. I'll be all right.

1025
01:05:49.886 --> 01:05:51.846
And you can't be
stupid like this.

1026
01:05:54.140 --> 01:05:56.684
So this is who Robert
screwed us over with?

1027
01:05:56.768 --> 01:05:57.808
The Che Guevara of Boston?

1028
01:05:57.852 --> 01:06:00.146
I mean. war must
be goin' pretty shitty

1029
01:06:00.229 --> 01:06:02.065
for you to be buying
from scumbags like him.

1030
01:06:02.148 --> 01:06:02.565
Yeah. it kinda has been.

1031
01:06:02.649 --> 01:06:04.901
The merch was bad.

1032
01:06:04.984 --> 01:06:06.670
and he obviously didn't
take "fuck off" for an answer.

1033
01:06:06.694 --> 01:06:08.854
- Gimme my knife.
- What do you need a car battery for?

1034
01:06:09.614 --> 01:06:11.240
- Don't.
- Not at her.

1035
01:06:13.284 --> 01:06:14.661
Point it at me.

1036
01:06:27.590 --> 01:06:28.466
And to answer your question.

1037
01:06:28.549 --> 01:06:30.189
I need it for a better
reason than you do.

1038
01:06:30.218 --> 01:06:33.054
No offense.
but Tommy's just one man.

1039
01:06:33.137 --> 01:06:35.306
- It's our business to know things.
- "To know things."

1040
01:06:35.390 --> 01:06:38.559
You're the cause of it. You
turned my own brother against me.

1041
01:06:38.643 --> 01:06:40.120
- Okay. Joel.
- That was a lot of gunfire.

1042
01:06:40.144 --> 01:06:41.372
- FEDRA's gonna be on the way.
- I know.

1043
01:06:41.396 --> 01:06:44.357
♪ ♪

1044
01:06:47.235 --> 01:06:49.404
We were gonna move
Ellie outta the zone tonight.

1045
01:06:49.487 --> 01:06:51.715
But we won't make it anywhere
like this. Not for a while anyway.

1046
01:06:51.739 --> 01:06:54.617
So now I'm thinkin'...

1047
01:06:54.701 --> 01:06:55.618
you're gonna do it.

1048
01:06:55.702 --> 01:06:57.054
- The hell we are.
- I'm not goin' with them!

1049
01:06:57.078 --> 01:06:58.246
- Let me take her.
- Tess...

1050
01:06:58.329 --> 01:06:59.247
we don't have time for this.

1051
01:06:59.330 --> 01:07:00.516
Marlene:
Oh. you don't have time?

1052
01:07:00.540 --> 01:07:01.290
- Who is she?
- Marlene: To you? She's cargo.

1053
01:07:01.374 --> 01:07:03.167
Joel: We don't
smuggle people. Sorry.

1054
01:07:03.251 --> 01:07:04.603
- I can do it.
- Kim. you don't have

1055
01:07:04.627 --> 01:07:06.003
a fuckin' ear
on your fuckin' head.

1056
01:07:06.087 --> 01:07:08.423
Could you please?

1057
01:07:08.506 --> 01:07:09.716
There's a team of Fireflies

1058
01:07:09.799 --> 01:07:11.318
waiting for her
at the old State House.

1059
01:07:11.342 --> 01:07:12.569
- (Joel scoffs)
- I know what's out there.

1060
01:07:12.593 --> 01:07:16.097
We were going with an entire
squadron for that very reason.

1061
01:07:16.180 --> 01:07:17.950
But now I don't have a
truck. I don't have a squadron.

1062
01:07:17.974 --> 01:07:19.308
FEDRA's five minutes away.

1063
01:07:19.392 --> 01:07:21.227
What I do have is you.

1064
01:07:21.310 --> 01:07:23.980
And I know what
you're both capable of.

1065
01:07:24.063 --> 01:07:25.523
For better or worse.

1066
01:07:28.443 --> 01:07:29.902
What are they capable of?

1067
01:07:29.986 --> 01:07:31.213
Marlene:
You get her there safely.

1068
01:07:31.237 --> 01:07:32.029
and they'll give you
what you need.

1069
01:07:32.113 --> 01:07:34.824
Not just a battery.
The whole thing.

1070
01:07:34.907 --> 01:07:37.452
Fueled-up truck. guns.
supplies. all of it.

1071
01:07:37.535 --> 01:07:38.953
I swear.

1072
01:07:39.036 --> 01:07:40.079
♪ ♪

1073
01:07:41.622 --> 01:07:42.957
I swear.

1074
01:07:50.757 --> 01:07:51.924
Asshole!

1075
01:07:52.008 --> 01:07:53.593
(Ellie sighs)

1076
01:07:57.847 --> 01:07:59.474
You trust her?

1077
01:07:59.557 --> 01:08:01.392
No. me neither.
but she seems desperate.

1078
01:08:01.476 --> 01:08:04.187
Firefly vehicle usually means
repurposed FEDRA stuff.

1079
01:08:04.270 --> 01:08:06.707
So better-than-decent chance
makin' it to Tommy in one of those.

1080
01:08:06.731 --> 01:08:08.149
The second we hand
that kid over...

1081
01:08:08.232 --> 01:08:09.585
Y'all talk it through.
but please remember

1082
01:08:09.609 --> 01:08:11.152
that I'm bleeding out.

1083
01:08:15.323 --> 01:08:17.533
Okay. Here's the deal.

1084
01:08:17.617 --> 01:08:18.719
We'll get her to your
crew at the State House.

1085
01:08:18.743 --> 01:08:20.870
But before we hand her over.

1086
01:08:20.953 --> 01:08:22.997
they give us
everything that we want.

1087
01:08:23.081 --> 01:08:24.999
If not. we kill her.
there and then.

1088
01:08:25.082 --> 01:08:27.168
- Deal.
- Really? That fast?

1089
01:08:27.251 --> 01:08:28.836
You are all that matters.

1090
01:08:28.920 --> 01:08:30.671
My team will not
jeopardize that.

1091
01:08:30.755 --> 01:08:32.507
Remember what I told you?

1092
01:08:32.590 --> 01:08:35.009
Now go get your backpack.

1093
01:08:35.092 --> 01:08:36.511
Now. Ellie.

1094
01:08:46.979 --> 01:08:48.022
Let's go.

1095
01:08:56.072 --> 01:08:57.406
Marlene: Joel...

1096
01:08:59.450 --> 01:09:02.495
don't fuck this up.

1097
01:09:03.329 --> 01:09:04.413
Please.

1098
01:09:05.414 --> 01:09:08.459
♪ ♪

1099
01:09:11.420 --> 01:09:12.713
(Marlene sighs)

1100
01:09:21.472 --> 01:09:22.014
(thundering)

1101
01:09:22.098 --> 01:09:25.226
(indistinct radio chatter)

1102
01:09:30.898 --> 01:09:32.441
♪ ♪

1103
01:09:48.082 --> 01:09:49.667
(door opens)

1104
01:09:51.836 --> 01:09:53.129
(Tess clears throat)

1105
01:09:55.673 --> 01:09:57.258
Give us a minute. all right?

1106
01:09:57.341 --> 01:09:58.384
What the fuck?!

1107
01:10:00.136 --> 01:10:02.096
So. what's the plan?

1108
01:10:02.179 --> 01:10:04.891
Tess: Hm. There's
not a lot of options.

1109
01:10:04.974 --> 01:10:07.101
There's the short way
or the long way.

1110
01:10:07.184 --> 01:10:07.935
The short way is pretty much...

1111
01:10:08.019 --> 01:10:10.313
Joel: That leaves the long way.

1112
01:10:10.396 --> 01:10:12.315
Things look bad.
we'll come up with something.

1113
01:10:12.398 --> 01:10:14.042
We'll have to drop.
head to Bill and Frank's.

1114
01:10:14.066 --> 01:10:17.445
Stock up on anything
we may need.

1115
01:10:17.528 --> 01:10:18.528
(conversation continues)

1116
01:10:18.571 --> 01:10:21.908
♪♪

1117
01:10:33.044 --> 01:10:35.212
Tess: We leave after
dark. Stay with the kid.

1118
01:10:37.173 --> 01:10:39.759
Joel:
Wait. Why do I have to... Tess.

1119
01:10:40.551 --> 01:10:41.802
Tess!

1120
01:10:49.268 --> 01:10:50.436
So. who's Bill and Frank?

1121
01:10:53.230 --> 01:10:55.983
The radio's a
smuggling code. right?

1122
01:10:56.067 --> 01:10:56.984
'60s song. they don't
have anything new.

1123
01:10:57.068 --> 01:10:59.320
'70s. they got new stuff.

1124
01:10:59.403 --> 01:11:00.613
What's '80s?

1125
01:11:07.620 --> 01:11:08.913
What are you doing?

1126
01:11:08.996 --> 01:11:09.914
- Killin' time.
- Well. what am I supposed to do?

1127
01:11:09.997 --> 01:11:12.416
I'm sure you'll figure that out.

1128
01:11:20.257 --> 01:11:21.884
Ellie: Your watch is broken.

1129
01:11:24.762 --> 01:11:26.847
(pages flipping)

1130
01:11:30.810 --> 01:11:32.395
(whooshing)

1131
01:11:35.606 --> 01:11:38.651
(helicopter hovering) - Ellie:
You mumble in your sleep.

1132
01:11:46.617 --> 01:11:48.417
I've never been on the
other side of the Wall.

1133
01:11:50.162 --> 01:11:51.247
Look how dark it is.

1134
01:11:58.796 --> 01:12:00.214
You guys go out there a lot?

1135
01:12:01.465 --> 01:12:03.426
- I guess.
- When was the last time?

1136
01:12:03.509 --> 01:12:05.136
(sighs) Maybe a
year. What's it matter?

1137
01:12:05.219 --> 01:12:06.887
Ellie: But you know where to go.

1138
01:12:08.055 --> 01:12:09.682
So we're gonna be okay.

1139
01:12:14.478 --> 01:12:17.523
Yeah.

1140
01:12:22.737 --> 01:12:23.612
So. what's the deal
with you anyway?

1141
01:12:23.696 --> 01:12:25.906
You some kinda bigwig's
daughter or somethin'?

1142
01:12:28.284 --> 01:12:29.910
Something like that.

1143
01:12:38.461 --> 01:12:40.880
Oh. the radio came on
when you were sleeping.

1144
01:12:41.505 --> 01:12:41.922
What?

1145
01:12:42.006 --> 01:12:42.882
What was the song?

1146
01:12:42.965 --> 01:12:44.967
Ellie: He kept sayin'. like.

1147
01:12:45.051 --> 01:12:47.553
like. "Wake me up
before you go-go"?

1148
01:12:48.679 --> 01:12:50.806
(softly): Shit.

1149
01:12:50.890 --> 01:12:52.349
Gotcha.

1150
01:12:52.433 --> 01:12:54.518
'80s means trouble.

1151
01:12:55.436 --> 01:12:58.481
Code broken.

1152
01:12:59.065 --> 01:13:02.068
- Listen...
- (door opens)

1153
01:13:03.903 --> 01:13:05.196
(door closes)

1154
01:13:06.864 --> 01:13:09.325
The spot under
Lancaster looks good.

1155
01:13:09.408 --> 01:13:11.368
- You got a jacket in your pack?
- Yeah.

1156
01:13:11.452 --> 01:13:14.121
Okay. get it.
It's time to go.

1157
01:13:17.875 --> 01:13:20.920
♪ ♪

1158
01:13:25.925 --> 01:13:27.635
Voice (over speaker):
<i>...mandatory curfew</i>

1159
01:13:27.718 --> 01:13:30.221
<i>to fight infection
and insurrection.</i>

1160
01:13:33.057 --> 01:13:35.142
<i>Observe mandatory curfew</i>

1161
01:13:35.226 --> 01:13:38.312
<i>to fight infection
and insurrection.</i>

1162
01:13:38.395 --> 01:13:40.231
(siren buzzes)

1163
01:13:54.995 --> 01:13:57.832
(helicopter hovering)

1164
01:14:00.918 --> 01:14:02.503
(grunting)

1165
01:14:08.300 --> 01:14:09.343
♪ ♪

1166
01:14:13.264 --> 01:14:14.348
(vehicle departing)

1167
01:14:27.111 --> 01:14:29.697
Holy shit.
I'm actually outside.

1168
01:14:29.780 --> 01:14:31.073
- Tess: Jesus Christ.
- Oh shit.

1169
01:14:34.410 --> 01:14:37.997
Okay. we're gonna take the
left edge around the buffer zone.

1170
01:14:38.080 --> 01:14:40.875
You stay close
and you follow my lead.

1171
01:14:40.958 --> 01:14:43.377
Yeah. Yeah. of course.

1172
01:14:43.460 --> 01:14:45.045
Tess: Let's go.

1173
01:14:51.886 --> 01:14:53.512
♪ ♪

1174
01:15:08.319 --> 01:15:10.571
(vehicle passes)

1175
01:15:18.662 --> 01:15:20.247
(thunder rumbling)

1176
01:15:28.005 --> 01:15:30.507
(rain pattering)

1177
01:15:30.591 --> 01:15:31.634
(metal clanking)

1178
01:15:36.472 --> 01:15:37.556
(helicopter passes)

1179
01:15:47.483 --> 01:15:48.525
♪ ♪

1180
01:15:58.869 --> 01:16:00.329
(thundering)

1181
01:16:08.212 --> 01:16:10.089
(urinating)

1182
01:16:15.719 --> 01:16:16.887
What the hell?

1183
01:16:16.971 --> 01:16:18.430
Hey. hey!
Don't. don't. don't move.

1184
01:16:18.514 --> 01:16:20.140
(zips trousers)

1185
01:16:20.224 --> 01:16:23.269
Don't move!

1186
01:16:27.398 --> 01:16:29.149
You gotta be shittin' me.

1187
01:16:29.233 --> 01:16:31.110
- Okay. let's talk this out.
- Turn around.

1188
01:16:31.193 --> 01:16:33.546
- Joel: Hold on...
- Get on your fuckin' knees. Get on your fuckin' knees!

1189
01:16:33.570 --> 01:16:35.173
- Now hold on...
- What did I fuckin' tell you. man?

1190
01:16:35.197 --> 01:16:36.824
I said stay the fuck home.

1191
01:16:36.907 --> 01:16:38.492
Get on your knees!

1192
01:16:38.575 --> 01:16:40.415
Just get on your knees.
just get on your knees.

1193
01:16:40.452 --> 01:16:42.371
Listen. you let us
do this run...

1194
01:16:42.454 --> 01:16:44.832
we'll split the cards with you.

1195
01:16:44.915 --> 01:16:46.059
- Lee: Oh. will you?
- Tess: Yeah.

1196
01:16:46.083 --> 01:16:46.834
I'm so blessed.

1197
01:16:46.917 --> 01:16:49.586
Hands on your head.
Eyes forward.

1198
01:16:49.670 --> 01:16:50.879
Hands on your head!

1199
01:16:54.550 --> 01:16:56.927
- Really. man?
- Yep. We're doin' this by the book.

1200
01:16:58.220 --> 01:16:59.722
- Tess: Jesus Christ.
- (scanner zaps)

1201
01:16:59.805 --> 01:17:01.640
All right.
What about three-quarters?

1202
01:17:01.724 --> 01:17:03.225
- (beeps)
- Unauthorized exit.

1203
01:17:03.309 --> 01:17:05.311
They'll hang you for that.

1204
01:17:05.394 --> 01:17:06.854
Fine. Everythin'
off of this run.

1205
01:17:06.937 --> 01:17:09.231
- and half off on all of the pills.
- Half off?

1206
01:17:09.315 --> 01:17:10.774
- (scanner beeps)
- All off.

1207
01:17:10.858 --> 01:17:11.734
Risk my job for half off.

1208
01:17:11.817 --> 01:17:13.819
- (scanner zaps)
- Outta your fuckin' mind...

1209
01:17:13.902 --> 01:17:14.921
- (Ellie screams)
- Tess: Ellie. Ellie!

1210
01:17:14.945 --> 01:17:17.698
- Ellie. what the...
- Lee: (groans) Fuckin' bitch!

1211
01:17:17.781 --> 01:17:19.575
Fuck!
(groans)

1212
01:17:19.658 --> 01:17:21.744
- Get out of the fuckin' way!
- Whoa. whoa!

1213
01:17:23.621 --> 01:17:25.122
We can fix this.

1214
01:17:25.205 --> 01:17:26.248
Move.

1215
01:17:26.707 --> 01:17:29.752
♪ ♪

1216
01:17:30.294 --> 01:17:33.339
Move.

1217
01:17:39.136 --> 01:17:40.721
(Joel shouts)

1218
01:17:42.181 --> 01:17:44.933
(grunting)

1219
01:17:55.611 --> 01:17:56.695
(heavy breathing)

1220
01:18:06.038 --> 01:18:09.124
♪ ♪

1221
01:18:09.208 --> 01:18:10.751
No. no!
No. I'm not sick!

1222
01:18:10.834 --> 01:18:12.520
- Joel! Joel. Joel!
- I am not sick! I'm not sick!

1223
01:18:12.544 --> 01:18:15.214
Look! Look!
This is three weeks old.

1224
01:18:15.297 --> 01:18:17.424
Nobody lasts more than a day!

1225
01:18:17.508 --> 01:18:19.968
Does this look
a day old to you?!

1226
01:18:20.052 --> 01:18:22.113
- You would've killed me!
- Tess: I should fucking kill you!

1227
01:18:22.137 --> 01:18:25.307
- When did it happen?
- It doesn't matter! You have to trust me!

1228
01:18:25.391 --> 01:18:28.644
- They're gonna catch us if we don't run!
- (siren wailing)

1229
01:18:28.727 --> 01:18:32.106
Joel. we gotta move.
We gotta move. Joel!

1230
01:18:32.189 --> 01:18:35.401
(distant chatter)

1231
01:18:35.484 --> 01:18:36.693
♪ ♪

1232
01:18:41.323 --> 01:18:44.118
(Tess grunting)

1233
01:18:44.493 --> 01:18:46.078
Joel!

1234
01:18:48.622 --> 01:18:49.665
♪ ♪

1235
01:19:00.008 --> 01:19:01.802
(thunder rumbling)

1236
01:19:01.885 --> 01:19:04.638
(radio turns on. static)

1237
01:19:04.721 --> 01:19:07.724
("Never Let Me Down Again"
by Depeche Mode plays on radio)

1238
01:19:17.234 --> 01:19:20.154
♪ ♪

1239
01:19:36.295 --> 01:19:41.550
<i>♪ I'm taking a ride
with my best friend ♪</i>

1240
01:19:45.387 --> 01:19:50.350
<i>♪ I hope he never
lets me down again ♪</i>

1241
01:19:54.438 --> 01:19:58.609
<i>♪ He knows where
he's taking me ♪</i>

1242
01:19:58.692 --> 01:20:03.363
<i>♪ Taking me where I want to be ♪</i>

1243
01:20:03.447 --> 01:20:07.701
<i>♪ I'm taking a ride
with my best friend ♪</i>

1244
01:20:21.465 --> 01:20:24.551
<i>♪ We're flying high ♪</i>

1245
01:20:24.635 --> 01:20:29.640
<i>♪ We're watching
the world pass us by ♪</i>

1246
01:20:31.141 --> 01:20:33.268
<i>♪ Never want to come down ♪</i>

1247
01:20:33.352 --> 01:20:38.649
<i>♪ Never want to put my feet
back down on the ground ♪</i>
